01:11:11.075 --> 01:11:13.023
mileage, and the
sales person there's

01:11:13.023 --> 01:11:14.440
going to tell you
this is the best

01:11:14.440 --> 01:11:15.648
investment I'm going to make.

01:11:15.648 --> 01:11:17.543
I think if they actually
ran the numbers,

01:11:17.543 --> 01:11:19.210
like you did in class,
in front of them,

01:11:19.210 --> 01:11:23.060
and they told them it's never
going to break even, never

01:11:23.060 --> 01:11:23.950
pay for itself.

01:11:23.950 --> 01:11:29.830
I think they might not want
to still be seen [INAUDIBLE]..

01:11:29.830 --> 01:11:33.040
SUSAN SILBEY: I didn't think the
argument was, about the Prius,

01:11:33.040 --> 01:11:34.870
that it wouldn't be
environmentally good.

01:11:34.870 --> 01:11:38.990
They just never get
the savings back.

01:11:38.990 --> 01:11:41.740
But so you two are
not disagreeing.

01:11:41.740 --> 01:11:44.353
You're offering two
different motivations.

01:11:44.353 --> 01:11:47.020
AUDIENCE: I just think their
own economical well-being

01:11:47.020 --> 01:11:49.810
would overpower their
want to be environmental.

01:11:49.810 --> 01:11:51.880
SUSAN SILBEY: Well,
that's a hypothesis.

01:11:51.880 --> 01:11:56.140
That's a hypothesis which is
challenged by all the Priuses.

01:11:56.140 --> 01:11:57.730
Oh, you're saying
they don't know.

01:11:57.730 --> 01:11:58.397
They don't know.

01:11:58.397 --> 01:11:59.855
PROFESSOR: There's
also a question,

01:11:59.855 --> 01:12:02.110
there are hybrids available
