01:12:14.030 --> 01:12:16.990
that are indistinguishable
from a distance.

01:12:16.990 --> 01:12:20.680
SUSAN SILBEY: And that would
not serve Max's reason,

01:12:20.680 --> 01:12:23.990
because everybody has
to know that you are--

01:12:23.990 --> 01:12:25.240
PROFESSOR: Not many people do.

01:12:25.240 --> 01:12:26.657
You don't buy it
for Max's reason,

01:12:26.657 --> 01:12:28.830
because nobody can tell
you made the purchase.

01:12:28.830 --> 01:12:30.900
And the sales are less.

01:12:30.900 --> 01:12:32.580
SUSAN SILBEY: Jacob
and then Charlotte.

01:12:32.580 --> 01:12:34.770
AUDIENCE: I would say
there's kind of a threshold.

01:12:34.770 --> 01:12:36.670
Once so many Priuses
were sold, they

01:12:36.670 --> 01:12:38.580
became a thing in advertising.

01:12:38.580 --> 01:12:40.482
When someone thought,
I need to buy a hybrid.

01:12:40.482 --> 01:12:41.440
They though of a Prius.

01:12:41.440 --> 01:12:42.945
They didn't think
of other hybrids.

01:12:42.945 --> 01:12:44.070
SUSAN SILBEY: I'll confess.

01:12:44.070 --> 01:12:46.740
I didn't know, for a long
time, there were others.

01:12:46.740 --> 01:12:48.600
I just saw the Priuses.

01:12:48.600 --> 01:12:51.690
So I was one of those people who
don't recognize the ones that

01:12:51.690 --> 01:12:55.620
are not styled differently.

01:12:55.620 --> 01:12:56.630
That's right.

01:12:56.630 --> 01:12:57.880
That's right.

01:12:57.880 --> 01:12:59.255
AUDIENCE: I was
just going to say

01:12:59.255 --> 01:13:02.400
