01:13:20.650 --> 01:13:23.130
But also because I
live in Oklahoma.

01:13:23.130 --> 01:13:24.040
So I drive a lot.

01:13:24.040 --> 01:13:26.757
And I wanted to not have to
pay a lot of money for gas.

01:13:26.757 --> 01:13:27.840
And that was my reasoning.

01:13:27.840 --> 01:13:30.663
And I would have never
considered running the numbers.

01:13:30.663 --> 01:13:32.580
SUSAN SILBEY: You just
believe what they told.

01:13:32.580 --> 01:13:34.200
AUDIENCE: Yeah,
and then also, just

01:13:34.200 --> 01:13:36.283
because when you
think of hybrid,

01:13:36.283 --> 01:13:38.700
you think of Prius, because
of their advertising strategy.

01:13:38.700 --> 01:13:41.040
It's not like I wasn't
wanting to buy it

01:13:41.040 --> 01:13:43.622
just because I thought it
would make people think that I

01:13:43.622 --> 01:13:44.830
was environmentally friendly.

01:13:44.830 --> 01:13:47.310
It was because I thought, oh,
maybe I wanted a hybrid car.

01:13:47.310 --> 01:13:49.840
I should get a Prius, because
that's the only one I know of.

01:13:49.840 --> 01:13:52.920
SUSAN SILBEY: I want to get on
Max's side for just a moment.

01:13:52.920 --> 01:13:57.060
Because I think that
people don't just

01:13:57.060 --> 01:14:00.210
buy things because
they're efficient,

01:14:00.210 --> 01:14:03.430
or because they're a
better economic deal.

01:14:03.430 --> 01:14:07.050
You cannot explain
the fashion industry.

01:14:07.050 --> 01:14:12.270
You cannot explain celebrity.

01:14:12.270 --> 01:14:15.180
It's not about
economic efficiency.

01:14:15.180 --> 01:14:19.410
I mean, you don't need to
have the number of sweaters

01:14:19.410 --> 01:14:20.580
and shoes.

01:14:20.580 --> 01:14:23.085
They don't wear out.

01:14:23.085 --> 01:14:26.640
You don't have to change
