their performance is lousy,
terrible gas mileage.

01:14:46.470 --> 01:14:48.960
SUSAN SILBEY: And why
do people buy them?

01:14:48.960 --> 01:14:51.240
Because

01:14:51.240 --> 01:14:54.252
AUDIENCE: Ford F150 is still the
best selling care in America.

01:14:54.252 --> 01:14:55.710
And people like
trucks, people like

01:14:55.710 --> 01:14:59.540
to be seen in high, big vehicles
to make them look wealthy.

01:14:59.540 --> 01:15:01.200
And they go outdoors--

01:15:01.200 --> 01:15:03.960
SUSAN SILBEY: It's called
status and approval.

01:15:03.960 --> 01:15:06.630
Sid, and then Andrew.

01:15:06.630 --> 01:15:10.080
AUDIENCE: I think has to do with
everyone's personal utility,

01:15:10.080 --> 01:15:12.260
[INAUDIBLE].

01:15:12.260 --> 01:15:14.010
SUSAN SILBEY: So where
did that personal--

01:15:14.010 --> 01:15:16.440
let's get to the
basis of this lecture.

01:15:16.440 --> 01:15:19.860
Where did that personal
utility come from?

01:15:19.860 --> 01:15:23.602
AUDIENCE: I mean, I'm sure like
it has to do with group theory,

01:15:23.602 --> 01:15:25.560
and which group you want
to be associated with.

01:15:25.560 --> 01:15:28.500
But there are different groups.

01:15:28.500 --> 01:15:30.570
And different people
might buy different things

01:15:30.570 --> 01:15:31.810
for different reasons.

01:15:31.810 --> 01:15:36.290
SUSAN SILBEY: And do we choose
all the groups we belong to?

01:15:36.290 --> 01:15:37.400
Come on.

01:15:37.400 --> 01:15:39.560
I mean, no.

01:15:39.560 --> 01:15:41.750
You can't say, just
look around this room,

01:15:41.750 --> 01:15:45.710
you can't say we all choose
